  "abstract": "The Board and the Commission jointly are adopting technical amendments to Regulation R, which the Agencies jointly adopted in September 2007. Regulation R implements certain of the exceptions for banks from the definition of the term \"broker\" in section 3(a)(4) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (\"Exchange Act\"), as amended by the Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act (\"GLBA\"). The technical amendments correct cross-references and other typographical errors in the regulation.",
